This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with training Binarized Neural Networks (BNNs) on the high resolution ImageNet ILSVRC-2102 dataset classification task. Additionally, it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the strategies used in network training. The paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it deals with neural networks, and the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories as it involves classification tasks.
